'How can I setup lamp server on Manjaro 20.2.2 ',/* title */
'how-can-i-setup-lamp-server-on-manjaro-20-2-2', /* Slug */

'
<p>
<b>Dear</b> friends it''s 26 Jan 2021 I am completely install manjaro-i3 as I 
have been very tied of doing some config on my manjaro kde or xfce so my config 
on i3 is quite simple this time just after newly install then I update the system
by using "pamac tray" which is come with manjaro-i3 already so really really minimal
config for me</p>
<p>
any way! before I go much more far far from this point this post will talk about 
'' how can I setup lamp server on majaro 20.2.2 '' which I mostly copy from this website
: ''https://forum.manjaro.org/t/howto-install-apache-mariadb-mysql-php-lamp/13000 ''



</p>
'
, /* excerpt */
'

<div class="container">

<img src="https://i1.wp.com/www.linuxandubuntu.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Install-LAMP-On-Manjaro.png?resize=960%2C540" 
class="responsive">


<p>I only have a bad example here so the video is may not look as professional as it''s 
suppose to be but any way you don''t have to read this too much 


</p>
<div class="video-container">
<iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/vvQCz2NK_80" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div>

<p>Hopefully you have learn something from this thank you</p>

</div>


',/* The post body */


